# Python build artifacts (sonar_pipeline.py is invoked directly; never commit caches)
__pycache__/
*.pyc
*.pyo

# Runtime artifacts produced by run_sonarqube_scan.sh that must never be committed.
# The driver writes transient debug dumps and a regenerated properties file next
# to itself; these are reproducible from a fresh run. AAP §0.6.2.4 mandates that
# sonar-project.properties is "Not committed to the repository", and the QA
# Checkpoint 1 MINOR finding (Issue #3) confirmed that committing this file
# leaves the working tree dirty after every run. Keeping it gitignored here
# preserves the run-time audit value of the file while satisfying AAP §0.3.2
# ("source tree byte-identical pre- and post-run").
sonar-issues-raw.json
sonar-scanner-output.log
sonar-project.properties
.scannerwork/
